The Herald Mugello. — Lewis Hamilton moved to within one victory of Michael Schumacher’s record after winning a dramatic Tuscan Grand Prix which was red flagged twice. Hamilton collected his 90th career win, taking the chequered flag 4.8 seconds clear of Valtteri Bottas in the other Mercedes at Mugello. London-born Thai Alexander Albon finished third to claim his first podium. Hamilton also secured a bonus point for the fastest lap to increase his lead in the standings to 55 points. — telegraph.co.uk. 